The paper discusses the use of blockchain-based distributed ledger technology for data sharing agreements, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also mentions the use of machine learning systems, which can be classified under artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The architecture proposed in the paper involves the use of a decentralised environment, which can be related to distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the need for data accuracy and quality, which can be related to data management (cs.DB) and machine learning (cs.LG).
